configSetPrices.disclaimer:
Calculation

The information presented on this website is based on data available to us at the time. Design, specifications, price, and production dates are subject to change without notice and pertain specifically to Irish vehicles. Some features and options may be unavailable when your vehicle enters production. We will inform you of those features and options as soon as possible when we become aware of any.

Base price includes VAT. VAT rates are subject to change. Base price includes an estimate for the VRT (including the VRT relief of € 5.000), which may be subject to change once confirmed by the Irish Revenue Commissioners. Changes to the VRT amount will therefore have an impact on the cash price. As long as the VRT amount (including the VRT relief of € 5.000) has not been confirmed to you, any deposit paid by you is fully refundable.
configSetPrices.gas_disclaimer:
Electric Vehicle Incentives

Tesla is in the process of registering with the SEAI for an electric vehicle grant of €5,000 for private buyers and €3,800 for commercial buyers. Tesla vehicles also receive a €5,000 deduction in vehicle registration tax, low Motor Tax of €120 per annum and commercial buyers are eligible for an Accelerated Capital Allowance Scheme. EV incentives are subject to eligibility and availability. Learn more.

Petrol Savings

Electric vehicles are less expensive to fuel than petrol powered vehicles. The average person drives approximately 15,000 km and spends around € 1,500 on petrol per year. In comparison, the cost of electricity to power Model S over the same distance is four times lower. Over the five year average length of car ownership, that's approximately € 5,200 in petrol savings.

We've assumed a fuel economy of 7.7l/100km for a comparable petrol powered car. We've also assumed the national average of € 0.16 per kilowatt hour for electricity, 10% charging on Tesla's Supercharger network enabling free long distance travel and € 1.3 per liter for premium petrol over the next five years.
configSetPrices.incentives_txt: The vehicle price includes a Government grant for a private buyer of €5,000. Electric vehicles purchased through a business are eligible for a €3,800 Government grant instead.
configSetPrices.name: IE 2016 NOVEMBER

ADPC2.description: Model S comes with a Type 2 charge port. Most charging stations require a Type 2 to Type 2 connector. Up to 23 miles of range per hour on a single-phase charge station at home. Up to 68 miles of range per hour when equipped with optional onboard 22 kW Dual Chargers (Note: charging rate also depends on power output of the charging station).

APE1.description:
Enhanced Autopilot adds new capabilities to the Tesla Autopilot driving experience. The enhancements include going from one to four cameras for greater accuracy, redundancy, and to see fast-approaching vehicles in adjacent lanes. In addition, 12 ultrasonic sonar sensors provide 360 degree coverage around your car with almost twice the range and resolution of the prior version.

The significantly increased sensor information is processed by a computer that is over 40 times more powerful than before. Your Tesla will match speed to traffic conditions, keep within a lane, automatically change lanes without requiring driver input, transition from one freeway to another, exit the freeway when your destination is near, self-park when near a parking spot and be summoned to and from your garage. That said, Enhanced Autopilot should still be considered a driver's assistance feature with the driver responsible for remaining in control of the car at all times.

Tesla's Enhanced Autopilot software is expected to complete validation and be rolled out to your car via an over-the-air update in December 2016, subject to regulatory approval.
APE1.name: Enhanced Autopilot

APF2.description:
This doubles the number of active cameras from four to eight, enabling full self-driving in almost all circumstances, at what we believe will be a probability of safety at least twice as good as the average human driver. The system is designed to be able to conduct short and long distance trips with no action required by the person in the driver’s seat. For Superchargers that have automatic charge connection enabled, you will not even need to plug in your vehicle.

All you will need to do is get in and tell your car where to go. If you don’t say anything, the car will look at your calendar and take you there as the assumed destination or just home if nothing is on the calendar. Your Tesla will figure out the optimal route, navigate urban streets (even without lane markings), manage complex intersections with traffic lights, stop signs and roundabouts, and handle densely packed freeways with cars moving at high speed. When you arrive at your destination, simply step out at the entrance and your car will enter park seek mode, automatically search for a spot and park itself. A tap on your phone summons it back to you.

Please note that Self-Driving functionality is dependent upon extensive software validation and regulatory approval, which may vary widely by jurisdiction. It is not possible to know exactly when each element of the functionality described above will be available, as this is highly dependent on local regulatory approval. Please note also that using a self-driving Tesla for car sharing and ride hailing for friends and family is fine, but doing so for revenue purposes will only be permissible on the Tesla Network, details of which will be released next year.
APF2.name: Full Self-Driving Capability

AU01.description:
Wrap your cabin in a pristine and powerful soundstage. This upgrade includes a larger amplifier, a subwoofer and 12 precisely positioned speakers to faithfully reproduce sound and deliver it directly to your ears and those of your passengers. This is a custom-designed audiophile-quality system that takes best advantage of the interior and ultra-quiet motors of Model S. The result is a listening experience that is unique in the automotive world, besting much more expensive systems in head-to-head comparisons. The package includes:

  • 12 speakers with neodymium magnets including an 8" subwoofer
AU01.name: Ultra High Fidelity Sound
